# UI & Component Rules

## Design Token System

All visual values (colors, font, radius) are CSS custom properties in `src/app/globals.css`.
These are the **single source of truth** — Tailwind utilities are just aliases for them.

```
globals.css :root / .dark   ← define CSS custom properties (the source)
globals.css @theme inline   ← maps CSS variables to Tailwind utilities
Component className          ← uses Tailwind utilities (bg-background, text-primary, etc.)
```

**Never hardcode color hex values in components.** Use semantic Tailwind classes:

| Token class | Resolves to |
|---|---|
| `bg-background` | Page background |
| `bg-background-subtle` | Slightly off-white / off-black surface |
| `text-foreground` | Primary text |
| `text-foreground-muted` | Secondary/subdued text |
| `border-border` | Default border |
| `bg-primary` | Brand accent color |
| `text-primary` | Brand accent text |
| `bg-surface` | Card / panel background |
| `bg-surface-hover` | Hover state for surfaces |

## Dark Mode

- Class-based via next-themes (`attribute="class"`)
- `@variant dark (&:is(.dark *))` in globals.css enables `dark:` Tailwind prefix
- `suppressHydrationWarning` on `<html>` prevents the theme flash warning

## Theming — How to Retheme

1. Open `src/app/globals.css`
2. Update values in `:root` (light theme) and `.dark` (dark theme)
3. Done — all components pick up the change automatically

## Component Conventions

- Accept `className` prop on all reusable components for external extensibility
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional/merged class strings
- Use semantic HTML (`<main>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<section>`, `<article>`)
- Add `aria-label` and `aria-hidden` attributes where appropriate

## Do Not

- Do not add icon libraries — use inline SVG for now, add an icon library when it becomes worth the bundle cost
- Do not add animation/motion libraries — use Tailwind transitions for simple cases
- Do not add component libraries (shadcn, Radix, etc.) without discussion — add them when the design is defined
